## 🚀 DEPLOYMENT - KNOW THIS BY HEART

### Deployment Targets

| Target             | URL                  | What it serves                        |
| ------------------ | -------------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| `ferni-prod`       | ferni-prod.web.app   | Firebase Hosting (app)                |
| `johnb-app`        | app.ferni.ai         | Firebase Hosting (app, custom domain) |
| `ferni-landing`    | ferni.ai             | Landing page                          |
| `bogle-ui`         | (Cloud Run)          | Backend APIs                          |
| `voiceai-agent-gce`| 34.134.186.63        | Voice Agent (GCE)                     |

### After Making Changes - ALWAYS DEPLOY

When you finish implementing a feature, **proactively suggest the correct deploy command**:

| Files Changed                       | Deploy Command                | What it does                                |
| ----------------------------------- | ----------------------------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| `src/agents/**/*.ts` (voice agent)  | `npm run deploy:agent`        | Deploy voice agent to GCE                   |
| `src/**/*.ts` (backend)             | `npm run deploy:ui:async`     | Blue-green deploy UI backend                |
| `frontend-typescript/src/*`         | `npm run deploy:frontend`     | Deploys to BOTH ferni-prod AND app.ferni.ai |
| `frontend-typescript/firebase.json` | `npm run deploy:frontend`     | Updates Firebase rewrites                   |
| `promo/ferni-website/*`             | `npm run deploy:landing`      | Deploys landing page                        |
| Multiple areas                      | `npm run deploy:all`          | Deploys everything                          |

### ⛔ NEVER USE DIRECT GCLOUD DEPLOYS (PRE-COMMIT WILL BLOCK!)

**CRITICAL:** The pre-commit hook WILL BLOCK commits containing direct cloud commands!

| ❌ FORBIDDEN (blocks commit)          | ✅ REQUIRED                    |
| ------------------------------------- | ------------------------------ |
| `gcloud compute ssh ... docker run`   | `ferni deploy gce`             |
| `gcloud run deploy ...`               | `ferni deploy ui`              |
| `firebase deploy --only hosting`      | `ferni deploy frontend`        |
| `docker push gcr.io/...`              | `ferni deploy` (handles push)  |

**Enforcement:**
1. **Pre-commit hook** - Scans for direct cloud commands, blocks commit
2. **CI/CD** - Uses Ferni CLI internally
3. **Code review** - Run `pnpm quality:deploy` to scan codebase

**Why?** Direct deploys cause:
- "Runner initialization timed out" errors
- Choppy/broken audio
- Zombie revisions consuming resources
- No rollback capability
- Missed health checks

**Ferni CLI provides:**
- Blue-green deployment (zero downtime)
- Health check before traffic shift
- Automatic rollback on failure
- Old revision cleanup (no zombies)
- Disk cleanup on every deploy

### CRITICAL: Firebase Hosting Has TWO Sites

The frontend app is deployed to TWO Firebase Hosting sites simultaneously:

- `ferni-prod` → ferni-prod.web.app
- `johnb-app` → app.ferni.ai (custom domain)

**NEVER deploy to just one.** Always use `npm run deploy:frontend` which deploys to both.

### API Rewrites

If you add a new API endpoint to `ui-server.js`, you MUST also add a rewrite rule to `frontend-typescript/firebase.json` for BOTH targets (`ferni-prod` and `johnb-app`).

Example rewrite for new `/api/newfeature` endpoint:

```json
{
  "source": "/api/newfeature",
  "run": { "serviceId": "bogle-ui", "region": "us-central1" }
}
```

### CI/CD vs Manual Deploy

- **Push to main** → CI/CD auto-deploys Cloud Run (UI server only)
- **Voice Agent (GCE)** → Manual: `npm run deploy:agent`
- **Firebase Hosting** → Manual: `npm run deploy:frontend` or `npm run deploy:landing`

### Verification Commands

```bash
curl https://app.ferni.ai/health          # Check UI backend
curl https://app.ferni.ai/api/agents      # Check agents API
curl https://app.ferni.ai/spotify/status  # Check Spotify
curl http://34.134.186.63:8080/health     # Check voice agent (GCE)
npm run ops:logs                          # View voice agent logs
```

