## Code Review Checklist

Before submitting code, verify:

- [ ] Types are explicit (no implicit any)
- [ ] Error cases are handled
- [ ] Async operations are awaited
- [ ] Functions are < 80 lines
- [ ] Files are < 500 lines
- [ ] Names are descriptive
- [ ] Public APIs have JSDoc
- [ ] **NO console.log/warn/error** - use `createLogger()` from `utils/logger.js`
- [ ] UI components have HMR cleanup (`cleanupOrphanedElements`)
- [ ] Tests cover happy path and edge cases

## 🛠️ Starting Dev Servers in Cursor

For Cursor AI agents: Start each server in a **separate background terminal** so logs can be watched individually.

### 4 Required Servers

| Server | Port | Command |
|--------|------|---------|
| **Token Server** | 3001 | `pnpm token-server` |
| **UI Server** | 3002 | `pnpm ui-server` |
| **Vite Frontend** | 3004 | `cd apps/web && pnpm dev` |
| **Voice Agent** | LiveKit | `LOG_FULL_RESPONSES=true pnpm dev` |

### Quick Reference

Run `ferni dev cursor` to see commands for starting servers in separate terminals.

### Health Check After Starting

```bash
curl -s http://localhost:3001/health  # Token server
curl -s http://localhost:3002/health  # UI server
curl -s http://localhost:3004/ | head -c 50  # Vite
```

### Stop All Servers

```bash
ferni dev stop
```

## 🤖 AI Agent Guardrails

### Before EVERY Code Change

```bash
npm run typecheck     # MUST pass before editing more files
npm run lint          # MUST pass before suggesting deploy
npm run tokens:check  # MUST pass if touched design-system/
```

### Common AI Agent Mistakes (AVOID THESE)

| Mistake                  | Why It Happens             | Prevention                          |
| ------------------------ | -------------------------- | ----------------------------------- |
| Editing `*.generated.ts` | Looks like normal code     | CHECK filename for `.generated.`    |
| Hardcoded `#4a6741`      | Faster than looking up var | ALWAYS use `var(--color-ferni)`     |
| Adding `console.log`     | Quick debugging            | ALWAYS use `createLogger()`         |
| Wrong deploy command     | Similar names              | CHECK deployment table in CLAUDE.md |
| Direct `gcloud run deploy`| Seems faster              | **NEVER** - use `npm run deploy:*`  |
| Breaking imports         | Moving files               | Run `npm run typecheck` IMMEDIATELY |
| Duplicate DOM elements   | HMR re-initialization      | ADD `cleanupOrphanedElements()`     |
| Token drift              | Edited JSON but not synced | Run `npm run tokens:sync`           |

### If Pre-commit Fails

```bash
# Fix lint errors
npm run lint:fix

# Fix formatting
npm run format

# Fix token drift
npm run tokens:sync && git add -A

# Then retry commit
git commit -m "your message"
```

### Generated Files (NEVER EDIT DIRECTLY)

These files are auto-generated. Edit the SOURCE instead:

| Generated File                     | Edit This Instead                     |
| ---------------------------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| `animation-constants.generated.ts` | `design-system/tokens/animation.json` |
| `persona-colors.generated.ts`      | `design-system/tokens/colors.json`    |
| `sounds.generated.ts`              | `design-system/assets/sounds/`        |
| `tailwind.config.generated.js`     | `design-system/tokens/colors.json`    |
| `promo/.../design-tokens.css`      | `design-system/tokens/*.json`         |
| `brand/ferni-design-tokens.css`    | `design-system/tokens/*.json`         |

## Import Organization

Imports should be ordered:

1. Node.js built-ins (`fs`, `path`)
2. External packages (`@livekit/agents`)
3. Internal modules (`../services/`)
4. Relative imports (`./utils`)
5. Type imports (with `type` keyword)

```typescript
import { readFile } from 'fs/promises';

import { Agent } from '@livekit/agents';
import { z } from 'zod';

import { userService } from '../services/user.service.js';

import { formatDate } from './utils.js';

import type { UserProfile } from '../types/user.js';
```

## When In Doubt

1. **Readability over cleverness** - Code is read 10x more than written
2. **Explicit over implicit** - Make behavior obvious
3. **Composition over inheritance** - Prefer small, composable pieces
4. **Fail fast, fail loud** - Catch errors early with clear messages
5. **Test behavior, not implementation** - Tests should survive refactors
